column1: Question,Correct Answer,Wrong Answer 1,Wrong Answer 2,Wrong Answer 3
Which statement about functional interfaces is true?,Has exactly one abstract method,Has exactly one method (any type),Cannot have default methods,Must be marked with @FunctionalInterface
Which is true about private interface methods?,Allowed since Java 9,Allowed since Java 8,Not allowed in interfaces,Must be abstract
Which statement about interfaces is correct?,All methods are implicitly public,Methods can be private by default,Methods are protected by default,Methods can be package-private
Which is true about default methods?,Can be overridden in implementing class,Cannot be overridden,Must be overridden,Are always final
Which is true about enum constructors?,Always private (implicitly or explicitly),Can be public,Can be protected,Must be public
Which annotation marks a functional interface?,@FunctionalInterface,@Functional,@Interface,@SingleMethod
Which is true about interface fields?,Implicitly public static final,Can be non-final,Can be private,Can be instance variables
Which is true about private interface methods?,Can only be called from within the interface,Can be called by implementing classes,Are inherited,Must be static
Which statement about enums is correct?,Enums cannot extend classes,Enums can extend any class,Enums extend Enum by default and can extend others,Enums don't extend anything
Which is true about functional interfaces?,Can have multiple default methods,Can have multiple abstract methods,Cannot have static methods,Cannot have Object class methods
Which is true about static interface methods?,Not inherited by implementing classes or sub-interfaces,Inherited by implementing classes,Inherited by sub-interfaces,Must be overridden
